What you need to know:

Authorities fear Victoria state is on the brink of the third Covid-19 wave with the city's five-million residents ordered to remain at home from midnightState Premier Daniel Andrews said the Melbourne Park tennis venue would be considered a "work place" that could continue to function with limited staffSpectators, who had been permitted over the first five days in limited numbers, will no longer be allowed from Saturday and players, who are keen to continue, must follow strict new rules